00:00:03.540 --> 00:00:08.240
So as Usai just said, you know, the Bcl-2 inhibitors are clearly an active class of

00:00:08.240 --> 00:00:13.360
drugs in mantle cell lymphoma, but I would argue that their strongest role is in combination

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:15.160
with other active regimens.

00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:19.820
And I do think they make great combination partners for several reasons: they have a

00:00:19.820 --> 00:00:26.600
unique mechanism of action, they have an overall favorable safety profile, and there's preclinical

00:00:26.600 --> 00:00:31.540
evidence of synergy with the BTKI, which are one of the most active class of drugs in mantle

00:00:31.540 --> 00:00:33.040
cell lymphoma.

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:37.200
There's also already compelling clinical data with Venetoclax combinations in mantle

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:44.140
cell lymphoma, particularly with the BTK inhibitors, with or without anti-CD20 monoclonal antibodies,

00:00:44.140 --> 00:00:49.400
and I've listed a few examples of key studies here, including Sepetico, Oasis-1 and 2, Traverse

00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:52.100
and Ambovin.

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:56.600
And as also discussed just now, snorotoclax is a next-generation Bcl-2 inhibitor.

00:00:56.600 --> 00:01:03.220
With greater preclinical selectivity and potency compared with venetoclax.

00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:08.320
So in terms of clinical trials of snorotoclax-based combinations in mantle cell lymphoma, we only

00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:13.360
have this one trial, which is a phase one trial of snorotoclax and zanubrutinib.

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:21.020
Zanubrutinib was given as the standard dose, and then there were escalated doses of snorotoclax.

