00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:10.360
So based on this, there's the ongoing phase 3 celestial trial in mantle cell lymphoma,

00:03:10.360 --> 00:03:16.360
which is a phase 3 randomized double-blinded study in patients with 1 to 5 prior lines of treatment.

00:03:16.360 --> 00:03:22.360
No prior BCL2 inhibitors are allowed, and no prior covalent or non-covalent BTKI are allowed,

00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:25.360
unless the BTKI was stopped due to intolerance.

00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:31.360
Patients are randomized 1 to 1 to receive zanubrutinib alone or with snorotoclax.

00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:34.360
Zanubrutinib is given as the standard dose until progression.

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:41.360
And then snorotoclax is started in cycle 2, so we lead in with zanubmonotherapy for only 4 weeks.

00:03:41.360 --> 00:03:44.360
And then snorotoclax is continued for 2 years.

00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:46.360
And the primary endpoint is PFS.

00:03:46.360 --> 00:03:51.360
This trial is ongoing.

00:03:51.360 --> 00:03:57.360
And then another trial, this is led by the cooperative group and by Dr. Reem Karmali.

00:03:57.360 --> 00:04:00.360
This is actually still in development, it hasn't opened yet.

00:04:00.360 --> 00:04:05.360
But it's for patients with previously untreated mantle cell lymphoma who are 70 years or younger.

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:08.360
All patients start with zanubrutinib for 1 cycle.

00:04:08.360 --> 00:04:16.360
And in the main cohort, patients are randomized to a triangle-like approach with BR and zanubrutinib for 6 cycles,

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:20.360
and then receive maintenance rituksin and zanubrutinib for 2 years.

00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:27.360
And the other arm receives chemotherapy-free triplet regimen with zanubrutinib, snorotoclax, and obin for 12 cycles.

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:29.360
So kind of bovine-like, but with snorotoclax.

00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:33.360
And then go on to receive obin and zanubrutinib for a year and a half.

00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:38.360
This ends up being that the two treatment arms have similar treatment duration.

00:04:38.360 --> 00:04:43.360
And then there's a small cohort of patients with TP53 aberrant mantle cell lymphoma

00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:49.360
who will receive the triplet, same triplet, zanubrutinib, obin, and snorotoclax for 12 cycles.

00:04:49.360 --> 00:04:58.360
And then are randomized to maintenance obin for a year and a half in combination with zanubrutinib, or Glowfit with zanubrutinib.

00:04:58.360 --> 00:05:03.360
And zanubrutinib here is until progression for both arms in the TP53 cohort.

00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:11.360
Another trial is, this is actually an IST from Dana-Farber, led by Dr. Christine Ryan,

00:05:11.360 --> 00:05:18.360
also for patients with previously untreated mantle cell lymphoma who are eligible for high-dose citerabine,

00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:22.360
where patients receive 3 cycles of zanubrutinib and BR,

00:05:22.360 --> 00:05:26.360
and then 3 cycles of rituksin and high-dose citerabine without zanubrutinib,

00:05:26.360 --> 00:05:27.360
and then are randomized to zanubrutinib.

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:33.360
They are randomized to zanubrutinib alone or with snorotoclax for 2 years.

00:05:33.360 --> 00:05:39.360
And the primary endpoint is the rate of CR with triplet blood MRD negativity after 1 year of maintenance treatment.

00:05:39.360 --> 00:05:45.360
And then we heard about some of the basket trials that will include BTK degraders with snorotoclax,

00:05:45.360 --> 00:05:48.360
but these are not specific for mantle cell lymphoma yet,

00:05:48.360 --> 00:05:52.360
but I think this is a combination that also makes sense in mantle cell lymphoma.

00:05:52.360 --> 00:05:56.360
And that's it. Thank you.

